Polycarp Igathe has resigned as the Executive Vice President, Sales and Marketing at Vivo Energy. In an internal communication sent by Vivo Energy CEO Christian Chammas, the company's head announced Omar Benson as Igathe's replacement in an acting capacity. "We thank Polycarp for his contribution to Vivo Energy and wish him the very best for the future," Chammas said. Omar will now report directly to the CEO on an interim basis while also continuing with his current role as Head of Retail and CR Strategy and Projects.